-- NBA Free-Agent Guard Beno Udrih Signs Deal With New York Knicks
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-08-09T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-09/nba-free-agent-guard-beno-udrih-signs-deal-with-new-york-knicks.html
Free-agent point guard Beno Udrih
signed a contract with the  New York Knicks , General Manager Glen Grunwald said in a statement on the team’s website.  The National Basketball Association team did not disclose
terms of the agreement. ESPN said Udrih signed a one-year
agreement for $1.27 million without saying where it got the
information.  Udrih, 31, a native of Slovenia, has career averages of 9.1
points, 3.6 assists and 2.2 rebounds in 628 games covering nine
seasons with the  San Antonio Spurs , Sacramento Kings, Milwaukee
Bucks and  Orlando Magic . He won NBA championships with the Spurs
in 2005 and 2007.  “Beno is a solid addition to our backcourt, where he will
give us more depth and flexibility,” Grunwald said. “He is a
talented and experienced floor general who brings championship
experience to our locker room.”  Last season with the Bucks and the Magic, he averaged 8.2
points and 4.6 assists in 66 games.  To contact the reporter on this story:
